page.title: 05LAND COVER AT MEDMENHAM
page.content: This area of mainly woodland is bisected by the A4155 Marlow-Henley road. The woodland is mainly beech due to the chalk and flint deposits but oak,fir,pine,elderberry,silver birch and hawthorn are also found and in May many patches are covered in bluebells. It is the habitat of many small mammals such as squirrels and rabbits.It is well served by footpaths. Between 10.50 a.m and 11.50 a.m on the 4th July 1985 816 cars travelled along the road.This is much heavier traffic than usual due to the Henley Regatta. For Danesfield School see page 4.
